# Dev Tools Server Configuration
# This file documents all available environment variables for the dev tools server.
# 
# For local setup:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Replace paths with your machine's actual storage locations
# 3. Keep .env.local out of git (it's in .gitignore)

# ============================================================================
# Storage Paths
# ============================================================================
# Where infrastructure service data is stored on the host.
# On Windows with Docker Desktop: use forward slashes
# On macOS/Linux: use $HOME or full path
# 
# Recommendations:
# - Use dedicated directories outside project workspaces
# - Ensure adequate disk space (Ollama models can be large)
# - Back up these paths if they contain important data

OLLAMA_STORAGE_PATH=${HOME}/.ollama
SONARQUBE_STORAGE_PATH=${HOME}/.sonarqube

# ============================================================================
# Service Access (for projects connecting via Docker network)
# ============================================================================
# Use these connection strings when connecting from containers on internal-network.
# From host machine, use Traefik routes on http://localhost
# 
# Default values (no need to set unless customizing):
# OLLAMA_HOST=http://ollama:11434
# POSTGRES_HOST=postgres
# POSTGRES_PORT=5432
# POSTGRES_USER=sonar
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD=sonar
# SONARQUBE_URL=http://sonarqube:9000
# DOCS_MCP_URL=http://docs-mcp:6280

# ============================================================================
# Drone CI Configuration
# ============================================================================
# Drone requires integration with a Git provider (Gitea, GitHub, GitLab, etc.)
# Generate a random RPC secret for server-agent communication:
#   openssl rand -hex 16
# 
# For Gitea integration:
DRONE_GITEA_SERVER=
DRONE_GITEA_CLIENT_ID=
DRONE_GITEA_CLIENT_SECRET=
#
# For GitHub integration (alternative to Gitea):
# DRONE_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=
# DRONE_GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=
#
# Required: Shared secret between Drone server and agents
DRONE_RPC_SECRET=

# Optional: Create admin user automatically on first launch
# Format: username:admin_username,machine:false,admin:true,token:your_token
# Example: username:admin,machine:false,admin:true,token:secrettoken
DRONE_USER_CREATE=